RosesGivenOutOnTV(x) ::: Roses are given out on TV at time x.
OnBachelor(x) ::: x is on the Bachelor.
Rose(x) ::: x is a rose.
PortraysRealPeople(x) ::: x portrays the lives of real people.
RealityTVShow(x) ::: x is a reality TV show.
Show(x) ::: x is a show.
BreakingBad ::: Breaking Bad.

# Premises:
∃t (Monday(t) ∧ At8pm(t) ∧ RosesGivenOutOnTV(t))
∀x (RosesGivenOutOnTV(x) → (Rose(x) ∧ OnBachelor(x)))
∀x (OnBachelor(x) → PortraysRealPeople(x))
∀x (PortraysRealPeople(x) → RealityTVShow(x))
¬RealityTVShow(BreakingBad)

# Conclusion:
∀x ((RosesGivenOutOnTV(x) ∧ Show(x) ∧ ¬RealityTVShow(x)) → (∃t (Monday(t) ∧ At8pm(t) ∧ RosesGivenOutOnTV(x))))
